snippet.title: Baalveer Kasam Kaal - Baalveer S3 - Ep 2 - Full Episode - 19 Mar 2023
snippet.description:
Episode 2: Baalveer Kasam Kaal
---------------------------------------
When Himbaash Lok's evil fairy, Aageel attacks his mother, Baalveer saves her. It was later revealed that Udaaka Lok's chief Maha Mahi Mutaan was testing Baalveer's abilities. Everyone admires Baalveer's strength and how he dealt with Aageel. Meanwhile, Himbaash Lok's fairy, Aageel brags about her extraordinary magical abilities, known as "Maha Jadu," with which she is now capable of defeating the ultimate hero, Baalveer. Maha Mahi Mutaan of Udaaka Lok warns Baalveer about his impending arrival and advises him to cut ties with his mother. Why was Baalveer given such dire warnings? How will Baalveer defeat Udaaka Lok's new nemesis? Keep an eye out!

snippet.description:
Siva (Sunil) and Karthik (Naga Chaitanya) are brothers. Elder brother Siva is a timid and shy. He fears for everything. Karthik is a dynamic guy who is very protective of his elder brother. Siva gets the job of a cop when his cop father dies. Siva is transferred to a seashore town where crime rate is high. Karthik goes in the guise of Siva and combat with anti-social elements whenever such situation arises. The crime rate goes down and people start respecting Siva as their savior. The rest of the story is all about what happens when the villains come to know that Siva is a fearing man and he is protected by his brother.

snippet.title: Meri Bassai | ‡§Æ‡•á‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§¨‡§æ‡§∏‡•ç‡§∏‡•à | Ep - 796 | 28 Feb, 2023 | Nepali Comedy | Magne Buda, Benisha Hamal
snippet.description:
Meri Bassai is one of the longest and most popular Nepali comedy serials with 18 Years of broadcasting. Based on rural lifestyle and lower-middle-class people, the series represents many political and social issues on its episodes with educational comedy flavor. It is aired in Nepal Television at 8:50 PM and in YouTube at 9:30 PM every Tuesday. This show is produced by Media Hub Pvt. Ltd. 

The story is based on the rural lifestyle and lower-middle-class people. The show represents many political as well as social issues on its episodes with educational comedy flavour.

Production: Media Hub Pvt. Ltd.
Production Advisor: Som Dhital
Direction: Diwakar Bhandari
Editor: Rabin Bhatta
Sub-Editor: Ashok Chaudhary/Sarita Gautam
IT Manager/Publicity Design : Dibash Humagain
Production Manager : Keshav Kaji Baniya
Script Writer: Kunjan Bhattarai/Diwakar Bhandari
Camera: Rahul Rai
Makeup: Pabitra Bhattarai
Title song Writer: Shankar Adhikari 
Music/Singer: Chetan Sapkota

Artists: Laxmi Giri, Keshav Prasad Pandit(Surbir), Ramchandra Adhikari, Surendra K.C, Palpasa Dangol, Niru Khadka, Tika bhakta Jirel,  Lekhant Bhusal, Diwakar Bhandari, Binam Kandel, Madhu Acharya, Ramesh Magar, Sarswoti Fuyal, Dhirendra Chand and many more.

Guest Artist : Kedar Ghimire 'Magne Buda' & Benisha Hamal

en.description:
Meri Bassai is one of the longest and most popular Nepali comedy serials with 18 Years of broadcasting. Based on rural lifestyle and lower-middle-class people, the series represents many political and social issues on its episodes with educational comedy flavor. It is aired in Nepal Television at 8:50 PM and in YouTube at 9:30 PM every Tuesday. This show is produced by Media Hub Pvt. Ltd. 

The story is based on the rural lifestyle and lower-middle-class people. The show represents many political as well as social issues on its episodes with educational comedy flavour.

==== Why Herne Katha? ====
People behind Herne Katha spent 15 years of their lives doing journalism. One day they realised the need to tell more beautiful and inspiring stories of people, the real people. 

üëÄüëÄüëÄ Herne Katha üëÄüëÄüëÄ
Herne Katha is a web series produced by Tana Bana Digital in Nepal. We tell stories of people in the format of short documentaries. New episode of Herne Katha is published on  every  alternate Tuesdays (15 days) on YouTube. You can also watch Herne  Katha on Kantipur  Television every Tuesday 6:30 PM.

üé®üé®üé® For all Creatives üé®üé®üé®
